        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-01-20T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-01-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="749" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d749">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.0093/1–2049: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-01-20T13:00:00+08:00">January 20, 1949—1 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 20—4:17 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>153. Obviously news of meetings North Atlantic group has spread (see our 149,
                    January 19). Philippine Counselor informs us Burmese Ambassador called meeting
                    19th Egyptian, Indian and Philippine Ambassadors to discuss Foreign Office
                    request removal Canton. Each agreed recommend his government that Ambassador
                    remain Nanking, sending senior subordinate Canton after Chinese Government had
                    effectively removed there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
